- Second layer: 1 green rectangular block placed horizontally across the cylinders
- Third layer: 1 red cubic block
- Top layer: 1 blue cubic block

Counting blocks: 5 blocks in total
Spatial arrangement: The structure is built vertically with the cylindrical blocks as a foundation, followed by stacked blocks centered on top.

Required blocks from the dictionary:
- Two orange horizontal cylinders (index 13, 14)
- One horizontal green rectangular block (index 7)
- One red cube (index 4)
- One blue cube (index 1)

Assembly order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 13
    Step2: Move block with index 14
    Step3: Move block with index 7
    Step4: Move block with index 4
    Step5: Move block with index 1
}

This assembly sequence starts from the bottom up, creating a stable structure where each layer supports the blocks above it.
